dataCsv.Site_Description: The Checotah is a flattened wreck with many artifacts on site. On or around the forecastle deck are large tow bitts, the anchor windlass, a cargo winch (likely steam driven), donkey boiler, the catheads, an anchor which is partially buried. The rudder is under part of the stern. There also appears to be part of a wooden reinforcing arch in the hull and a number of reinforcing strapping beams also in the hull.
